    <stitle>CALIPER DISC BRAKES - CALIPER - ROTOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ROTOR</title>
        <para>The cast machined rotor (disc) is bolted to the hub assembly. Cooling fins cast between the two machined
            pad surfaces of the rotor allow air to flow between the rotor surfaces to cool the rotor while the wheel is
            turning. The rotors on both front and rear brake groups are protected by splash shields bolted to the wheel
            end anchor plates and axle flanges. For detailed information on rotors, refer to GROUP 04 - BRAKES,
            HYDRAULIC in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
